(CNN)The First Family of Sitcomedy is getting a visit from a former first lady. Michelle Obama will be guest starring in an episode of ABC's "black-ish," the beloved family sitcom that's heading into its eighth and final season. The show's social media pages posted a sneak peek at Obama's appearance on Thursday.  "We are honored to have trailblazer @michelleobama join us as an upcoming guest star," the show wrote on Instagram. A representative for the network tells CNN that Obama will be playing herself in the episode. "I've long been a fan of @BlackishABC's wit and all-around brilliance, and it was such a thrill to join in for an episode," Obama added on social media. "I can't wait for you all to see it!" The final season of "black-ish" is set to premiere in early 2022 on ABC. 